research_municipality_step.notes: Jacinto City, TX operates under a city manager form of government with an elected Mayor who presides over the City Council. The City Council is comprised of the Mayor and five Council Members. The Mayor's name is from a 2024 source, while the Council Members' names are from a 2021 source. Jacinto City has staggered elections, with the Mayor and two council positions up for election in odd-ending years, and the remaining three council seats in even-ending years.
